# Database Migrations

Migration system at `src/infrastructure/migration/`. Migration files at `src/migrations/`.

## Creating a new migration

File: `src/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.ts`

```typescript
import type { Db } from 'mongodb';
import type { IMigration } from '../infrastructure/migration/index.js';

const migration: IMigration = {
  description: 'Human-readable description',
  async up(db: Db): Promise<void> { /* apply changes */ },
  async down(db: Db): Promise<void> { /* revert changes */ },
};
export default migration;
```

## Rules

- Use raw `mongodb.Db` (from `'mongodb'` package), NOT Mongoose
- Both `up()` and `down()` MUST be idempotent (safe to run twice)
- Use `createIndex()` (no-op if exists) — never assume index absence
- Use `.catch(() => { /* index may not exist */ })` on `dropIndex` / `dropCollection` in `down()`
- Every new collection or index MUST have a migration
- Run `npm run migrate:up` before `npm start` in production/CI

## CLI commands

- `npm run migrate:up` — apply all pending (runs `tsx src/infrastructure/migration/migrate.cli.ts up`)
- `npm run migrate:down` — revert last applied
- `npm run migrate:status` — show applied vs pending
